results.definition: three times as great or many
examples: a claim for treble (or triple) damages

results.definition: having more than one decidedly dissimilar aspects or qualities; public preaching and private influence"- R.W.Emerson
examples: a double (or dual) role for an actor
the office of a clergyman is twofold
every episode has its double and treble meaning"-Frederick Harrison
our rent increased threefold in the past five years
